name: Two RCAF CF-18 Hornets Formation Landing at Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Happy Canada Day! These two CF-18 Hornets, part of 410 Squadron based in Cold Lake, Alberta, came in this afternoon from Edmonton to do a Canada Day flyover of Calgary after doing some flypasts around Edmonton. Here they are arriving in Calgary, in my first video of a CF-18 at YYC, having filmed the demo jet a couple times at airshows, but never at the international airport! Enjoy this LOUD formation arrival of these two jets!

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

FLIGHT INFO
Airline: Royal Canadian Air Force 410 Squadron
Aircraft: CF-18 Hornet (F18)
Livery: Standard RCAF grey with cougar emblem
Engines: 2× General Electric F404-GE-400
Registration: 188785 and 188786 
Route: Edmonton (YEG) - Calgary (YYC)
Callsign: Cougar 51
Runway used: 17R
Date filmed: July 1, 2017
Local time: 1545
